content: Got an invite to collaborate on an AI-driven risk model. This could be my entry into managing my own portfolio.
Spent the last few days refining my trading algorithm. It's now faster, but is it more ethical? That's the real question.
Had dinner with friends from NYU. Their support is grounding. I shared my struggles and they gave some sage advice.
Just turned 22. Reflecting on where I am, what I've lost, and what I'm gaining. This journey is just beginning.
Ran into an old friend on the subway. We laughed about old times, but I couldn't help but think about how much has changed.
Progress on the AI model is slow but steady. It's like watching grass grow, but with occasional breakthroughs.
Had a moment of doubt. Is my approach too aggressive? Maybe I need to balance speed with fairness in trading.
The collaboration is turning into something special. We're seeing real-time improvements in our risk model.
Just got a call from my mentor. They've recommended me for a position at a top quant trading firm.
I'm now officially working on a project that could redefine how we approach high-frequency trading.
Looking back at the past 60 days, I've grown so much. The city, my work, my life—it's all moving forward.
